00:54:56.440 --> 00:54:58.802
You can't let the casino notice.

00:54:58.802 --> 00:55:02.050
Now, people also looked at
another field, sports betting.

00:55:02.050 --> 00:55:04.910
Now, sports betting, this
is frequent of stuff.

00:55:04.910 --> 00:55:07.240
This is Bayesian stuff.

00:55:07.240 --> 00:55:12.080
It is a lot easier
to predict how

00:55:12.080 --> 00:55:15.680
people are going to bet than
how a game is going to come out.

00:55:15.680 --> 00:55:19.530
If you wanted to predictive
a game from first principles

00:55:19.530 --> 00:55:21.550
and figure out what the
proper point spread was,

00:55:21.550 --> 00:55:23.070
well, you've got a
big job ahead of you.

00:55:23.070 --> 00:55:23.490
It can be done.

00:55:23.490 --> 00:55:25.698
People have done it and made
some successful results,

00:55:25.698 --> 00:55:27.140
but that's a big job.

00:55:27.140 --> 00:55:29.470
Here's an easy observation
that was enough.

00:55:29.470 --> 00:55:32.730
In the 1970s, this was
enough to make money.

00:55:32.730 --> 00:55:35.360
Los Angeles Lakers
are a glamorous team.

00:55:35.360 --> 00:55:37.320
They were at the time.

00:55:37.320 --> 00:55:39.709
Los Angeles is a
big betting city.

00:55:39.709 --> 00:55:41.250
When the Lakers play
at home, there's

00:55:41.250 --> 00:55:43.860
a lot of money coming
in and betting on them.

00:55:43.860 --> 00:55:46.580
The point spread is going
to be too favorable.

00:55:46.580 --> 00:55:49.079
Bet against the
Lakers at home, right?

00:55:49.079 --> 00:55:50.870
Don't need a genius,
don't need a math PhD,

00:55:50.870 --> 00:55:51.640
don't need a computer.

00:55:51.640 --> 00:55:52.900
You can just figure this out.

00:55:52.900 --> 00:55:54.960
And patterns like this
are very easy to catch,

00:55:54.960 --> 00:55:58.160
but they're based on
understanding people.

00:55:58.160 --> 00:56:00.320
So the malcontents,
the introverts,

00:56:00.320 --> 00:56:02.810
the autistic people,
they all went here.

00:56:02.810 --> 00:56:06.022
The people who like people
went into sports betting.

00:56:06.022 --> 00:56:07.730
Now what happens if
you're sports betting

00:56:07.730 --> 00:56:08.646
and you're successful?

00:56:08.646 --> 00:56:10.080
What happens?

00:56:10.080 --> 00:56:14.140
Well certainly in those
days, they hire you.

00:56:14.140 --> 00:56:15.407
Right?

00:56:15.407 --> 00:56:15.990
They want you.

00:56:15.990 --> 00:56:17.720
Great, hey, you're winning?

00:56:17.720 --> 00:56:19.150
We want to take
advantage of that.

00:56:19.150 --> 00:56:20.170
We'll pay you a salary.

00:56:20.170 --> 00:56:20.861
You bet for us.

00:56:20.861 --> 00:56:22.860
And then the way they
would pay you, by the way,

00:56:22.860 --> 00:56:26.680
is they would let
you make bigger bets.

00:56:26.680 --> 00:56:29.520
And so you become part
of the organization.

00:56:29.520 --> 00:56:33.160
And pretty soon, you're running
your own bookmaking operation

00:56:33.160 --> 00:56:33.660
and so on.

00:56:33.660 --> 00:56:35.560
So these are social people.

00:56:35.560 --> 00:56:37.060
These are Bayesian people.

00:56:37.060 --> 00:56:38.770
These people are
betting on frequencies.

00:56:38.770 --> 00:56:41.340
These people are
betting on people.

00:56:41.340 --> 00:56:43.366
Both of them are learning
skills and techniques

00:56:43.366 --> 00:56:44.990
that nobody taught
in a classroom, that

00:56:44.990 --> 00:56:49.550
were totally generations ahead
of what statisticians were

00:56:49.550 --> 00:56:52.030
doing in academics, what people
were doing in econometrics,

00:56:52.030 --> 00:56:52.821
anything like that.

00:56:52.821 --> 00:56:55.460
These people were because
these people had to.

